# File Organization Standards

This document defines the standard locations and organization for different types of files in the Next.js 15 App Router project.

## Root Directory Structure

```
/web/
├── bin/              # Scripts and utilities
├── doc/              # Documentation
├── prisma/           # Database schema and migrations
├── public/           # Static assets
├── src/              # Source code
├── next.config.ts    # Next.js configuration
├── package.json      # Package configuration
├── tsconfig.json     # TypeScript configuration
└── README.md         # Project overview
```

## Scripts Location (`/web/bin/`)

All deployment, build, database, and utility scripts.

### Script Types and Locations

- **Installation Scripts**: `/web/bin/install.ts`
- **Build Scripts**: `/web/bin/optimize-build.js`
- **Database Scripts**: `/web/bin/pg_backup*.sh`
- **Deployment Scripts**: `/web/bin/sync_*.sh`
- **Package Management**: `/web/bin/upgrade_pkg.sh`

### Examples

```
/web/bin/
├── install.ts
├── optimize-build.js
├── pg_backup.sh
├── pg_backup_rotated2.sh
├── pg_backup_ship.sh
├── sync_from_production.sh
├── sync_to_production.sh
└── upgrade_pkg.sh
```

## Documentation Location (`/web/doc/`)

All project documentation, guides, and references.

### Documentation Types

- **Deployment Guides**: `DEPLOYMENT-*.md`
- **Setup Guides**: `*_SETUP.md`
- **Environment Configuration**: `ENVIRONMENT_VARIABLES.md`
- **Security**: `SECURITY.md`
- **Contributing**: `CONTRIBUTING.md`
- **Reference Materials**: `doc/refernces/`

### Examples

```
/web/doc/
├── DEPLOYMENT.md
├── DEPLOYMENT-postgres.md
├── ENVIRONMENT_VARIABLES.md
├── RECAPTCHA_SETUP.md
├── GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_COMPLETE_GUIDE.md
├── SECURITY.md
├── CONTRIBUTING.md
└── refernces/
```

## Source Code Structure (`/web/src/`)

### Actions (`/web/src/actions/`)

Server actions and feature-owned server helpers organized by domain. See [actions-vs-lib.mdc](mdc:web/.cursor/rules/actions-vs-lib.mdc) for what belongs here vs `lib/`.

```
src/actions/
├── admin/                    # Admin-related actions
│   ├── maint/               # Maintenance actions
│   ├── systemMessage/       # System message management
│   ├── user/                # User management
│   └── populate-*.ts        # Data population scripts
├── storeAdmin/              # Store admin actions
├── sysAdmin/                # System admin actions
├── store/                   # Store-related actions
├── user/                    # User-related actions
├── mail/                    # Email sending and queue management
├── geo/                     # Geolocation services
└── *.ts                     # Shared actions
```

**Naming Convention**: `verb-object.ts` (e.g., `get-store-by_id.ts`, `create-store-notification.ts`)

### App Router (`/web/src/app/`)

Next.js 15 App Router pages, layouts, and API routes.

```
src/app/
├── (root)/                  # Root route group
│   ├── account/            # User account management
│   ├── checkout/           # Checkout process
│   ├── order/              # Order viewing
│   ├── privacy/            # Privacy policy
│   ├── terms/              # Terms of service
│   └── unv/                # Universal landing pages
├── s/                       # Store route group
│   └── [storeId]/          # Dynamic store routes
│       ├── category/       # Category pages
│       ├── product/        # Product pages
│       ├── faq/            # Store FAQ
│       ├── support/        # Customer support
│       └── components/     # Store-specific components
├── api/                     # API routes
│   ├── auth/               # Authentication endpoints
│   ├── common/             # Common utilities
│   ├── payment/            # Payment processing
│   ├── store/              # Store API endpoints
│   ├── storeAdmin/         # Store admin API
│   └── sysAdmin/           # System admin API
├── auth/                    # Authentication pages
├── storeAdmin/              # Store admin dashboard
│   ├── (dashboard)/        # Dashboard route group
│   └── (root)/             # Store admin root
├── sysAdmin/                # System admin dashboard
├── css/                     # Global styles
├── i18n/                    # Internationalization
├── layout.tsx               # Root layout
└── not-found.tsx            # 404 page
```

**Route Groups**: Use parentheses `(group)` for organizing routes without affecting URL structure.

### Components (`/web/src/components/`)

Reusable UI components organized by category.

```
src/components/
├── ui/                      # shadcn/ui components
├── modals/                  # Modal dialogs
├── analytics/               # Analytics components
├── auth/                    # Authentication components
├── editor/                  # Rich text editors
├── store/                   # Store-specific components
└── *.tsx                    # Shared components
```

**Naming Convention**:

- Component files: `kebab-case.tsx` (e.g., `cart-summary.tsx`)
- Component names: `PascalCase` (e.g., `CartSummary`)

### Hooks (`/web/src/hooks/`)

Custom React hooks.

```
src/hooks/
├── storeAdmin/              # Store admin hooks
└── use-*.{ts,tsx}           # Custom hooks
```

**Naming Convention**: `use-feature-name.ts` (e.g., `use-cart.tsx`, `use-geo-ip.tsx`)

### Library (`/web/src/lib/`)

Shared infrastructure and **cross-route domain kernels** (not feature safe-actions). See [actions-vs-lib.mdc](mdc:web/.cursor/rules/actions-vs-lib.mdc).

**Three layers (pick one per module):**

| Layer | Location | What belongs |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Infrastructure | `lib/` root or integration folders (`payment/`, `otp/`, `mail/`, `auth.ts`, `prismadb.ts`) | SDKs, auth, DB, logging, plugins, delivery channels |
| Domain kernel | `lib/{domain}/` | Reusable business rules for one product concept, imported from multiple actions/routes **without** a safe-action or `*.validation.ts` |
| Feature logic | `actions/{actor}/{feature}/` | Mutations, page loaders, and helpers owned by store admin, storefront, sys admin, or account |

**`lib/{domain}/` (domain kernels):**

- Folder name: **singular** domain noun (`facility/`, `reservation/`, `shop/`, `notification/`).
- **Two or more** related modules in the same concern → **`lib/{domain}/`** (never a cluster of `lib/{domain}-*.ts` at the root).
- **`lib/` root** is **generic infrastructure only** (auth, DB, logging, request helpers, cross-cutting `utils.ts`). Do not add new domain-prefixed files at the root.
- File name: **kebab-case**, **verb-first** (`get-table-name.ts`, `get-effective-facility-business-hours.ts`, `compute-rsvp-stats.ts`).
- Inside `lib/{domain}/`, **drop redundant domain prefixes** from filenames (`lib/facility/get-table-name.ts`, not `lib/facility/facility-get-table-name.ts`).
- Prefer **one primary export** per file; split when a file grows past ~300 lines or mixes unrelated concerns.
- Put code here when it encodes **what the domain means** (resolve effective hours, map facility display name, token confirm rules) and is consumed from **two or more** of: `actions/`, `app/` server components, `app/api/`, `lib/` in the same domain.
- **Do not** colocate `*.validation.ts` or exported safe-actions under `lib/`.
- **Avoid** a single top-level `lib/{domain}.ts` for non-trivial logic — use `lib/{domain}/…` (same pattern as `lib/facility/get-effective-facility-business-hours.ts`).

**Examples:**

- `getTableName` (facility display name from a list + id) → `lib/facility/get-table-name.ts`, not `lib/getTableName.ts` or a generic `utils/` dump.
- `getServiceStaffData` (store-scoped staff list + booking filters) → `actions/store/reservation/get-service-staff-data.ts` (shared by store admin and storefront actions), **not** `lib/service-staff.ts`.
- `findOrCreateUserId` / phone normalization for store-admin customer flows → `actions/storeAdmin/storeAdmin/find-or-create-user-id.ts`, **not** `utils/user-find-or-create.ts`.
- `isCancellationWithinCancelHours` (pure policy) → `lib/reservation/cancel-hours.ts`; async validation with i18n → `actions/store/reservation/validate-cancel-hours.ts`.
- Request URL / search params / client IP → `lib/server-request.ts`; `actions/server-util.ts` is a thin `"use server"` re-export barrel for server actions only.
- Stripe webhooks, Twilio/Mitake OTP clients → `lib/payment/`, `lib/otp/` (infrastructure), not `actions/`.

**`types/` vs `lib/` vs `utils/`:**

- `types/` — serializable shapes, column DTOs, enums safe on client and server (`service-staff-column.ts`).
- `lib/{domain}/` — server-side domain rules that may use Prisma or other `lib/` integrations.
- `utils/` — **generic, domain-agnostic** helpers at **`utils/` root** only (`datetime-utils.ts`, `guid-utils.ts`, `error.ts`, `utils.ts`). **Do not** add **`utils/{domain}/`** folders; domain-specific helpers belong in **`lib/{domain}/`** when there are **two or more** related modules (e.g. `lib/reservation/cancel-hours.ts`, not `utils/rsvp-cancel-hours.ts` at root).
- **Import direction:** `actions/` may import `lib/` and `utils/`; `lib/` and `utils/` must **not** import `actions/`.

```
src/lib/
├── auth.ts                  # Authentication logic
├── auth-client.ts           # Client-side auth
├── prismadb.ts              # Database client
├── analytics.ts             # Analytics integration
├── logger.ts                # Server logging
├── client-logger.ts         # Client logging
├── server-request.ts        # Request URL, search params, client IP (no "use server")
├── utils.ts                 # General utilities (prefer domain folders for domain rules)
├── businessHours/           # Business hours logic (legacy camelCase path)
├── facility/                # Facility / table domain kernels (e.g. effective hours, display names)
├── product/                 # Product catalog helpers (slugs, specs JSON, customization utils)
├── credit/                  # Customer credit kernels (e.g. top-up bonus calculation)
├── store/                   # Store-level kernels (e.g. Pro vs Free tier checks)
├── reservation/             # RSVP/reservation kernels (stats, cancel policy, tokens, …)
├── waitlist/                # Waitlist session, local storage, called bell
├── service-staff/           # Staff schedule and facility-hours resolution
├── image/                   # Client image resize / remote URL helpers
├── shop/                    # Storefront catalog, cart, checkout helpers
├── notification/            # Template engine, channels, lifecycle payloads
├── otp/                     # OTP send/verify + SMS provider adapters
├── payment/                 # Payment plugins; stripe/, paypal/, linePay/ (linePay: legacy camelCase)
└── useTwZipCode2/           # Taiwan zip code utilities (legacy camelCase path; data/zip-code.ts)
```

### Providers (`/web/src/providers/`)

React context providers for global state.

```
src/providers/
├── i18n-provider.tsx        # Internationalization
├── session-provider.tsx     # Authentication session
└── theme-provider.tsx       # Theme management
```

### Types (`/web/src/types/`)

TypeScript type definitions.

```
src/types/
├── types.d.ts               # Global type definitions
├── bank3.ts                 # Bank-related types
└── enum.ts                  # Enumerations
```

### Utilities (`/web/src/utils/`)

Helper functions and utilities. **`utils/` root** holds **generic** modules only — **no** `utils/{domain}/` subfolders. **Two or more** modules for the same domain concern → **`lib/{domain}/`** (singular noun, kebab-case files; drop redundant domain prefix in the filename).

```
src/utils/
├── actions/                 # safe-action clients (safe-action.ts); not domain server actions
├── chinese-util.ts          # Chinese language utilities
├── datetime-utils.ts        # Date/time helpers
├── geo-ip.ts                # Geo IP utilities (may import @/lib/server-request)
├── guid-utils.ts            # GUID generation
├── is-admin.ts              # Admin session role check
├── error.ts                 # Error handling
└── utils.ts                 # General utilities
```

**Legacy:** flat `utils/rsvp-*.ts`, `utils/waitlist-*.ts`, and similar at root should move into **`lib/{domain}/`** when touched; do not add new domain-prefixed root files under `utils/`.

